ass=m><span class=title> Re: No-killing quests</span><hr size=1> Runner quest is part of bard epic.<br>
<br>
Other quests........<br>
<br>
Foraging quest in katta.  Results in +10% foraging scimmy.<br>
<br>
Registering with Trade Master Henry in Shadowhaven.<br>
<br>
Compass for walking the little kitty girl home in shar vahl.<br>
<br>
Healing for bux by Lashan Novashine.<br>
<br>
Healing for bogjuice and bandaids in Prime Healer's Temple in Qeynos.<br>
<br>
Taking note from Temple of Rodcet Nife to the Soulfire guy and back to Qeynos.<br>
<br>
The 'spawn a ton of giants at the kael entrance and gank noobs fighting there cuz I want faction' Wakening lands Kael faction quest.<br>
<br>
The toolbox from wenglawks to iceclad quest. <br>
<br>
<br>
There are TONS of quests that have no combat in them.  However, risk vs reward is not very high on most of them.  As an example of high risk vs reward in a courier quest:<br>
<br>
Black Sapphire + Ruby to Niblek in Chardok gets you a piece of the Kylong Medallion, which is part of the Veeshans Peak key quest.<br>
<br>
Enchanted soul jar to human skeleton in City of Mist gets you part of the Concussion spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
If it's a good courier quest, you're usually gonna have to kill all kinds of stuff in the way to get to where you can do the turn in.  That's as it should be.   What I really think are lacking are more of the higher end turn ins;  luclin seems to be a bigger step towards what was starting in velious.  nice, cool, scripted events.  10th ring war.  Grimling quests.  Ring of Fire.  Stuff that you can have fun doing, rather than another campfest marathon of hacking and slashing.  'Did the rare spawn?'  'Yes.'  &quot;Did it drop what you need?'  &quot;no.'  'crud.'  'yup'  'afk, getting 3 more bags of chips and a couple two liters. we gonna be here a while more.'<br>
Give us more cool triggered events/ quests.  Screw this campfest garbage.<br>
